OL,3,CCould the debate over this senior
OL,4,Cpolitician's role hurt a fair trial?
OL,6,FWhile P&R has framed the policy letter
OL,7,Fto avoid any commentary on the case,
OL,8,Fand argue that it is purely concerned
OL,9,Fwith the 'practical implications' of
OL,10,FDeputy Le Tocq being absent, in a
OL,11,Fforum where deputies are protected by
OL,12,Fparliamentary privilege, anything
OL,13,Fcould be said by anyone.
OL,15,FIf enough is said to make a fair trial
OL,16,Fimpossible, the legal case could be
OL,17,Fderailed completely.
OL,19,FIt's an almost impossible situation,
OL,20,Fand a real test of Guernsey's ability
OL,21,Fto split judiciary and government.
